that would be obstruction.

18:24.036 --> 18:27.840 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Because that would --
that would
satisfy the corruptly -- acting
corruptly?

18:27.873 --> 18:31.210 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM JEFFRESS: That would be
an improper
purpose, yes, to keep a witness
quiet.

18:31.243 --> 18:37.583 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: And, in this
discussion, can a
president, Mr. Jeffress, can a
president be

18:37.616 --> 18:38.584 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
indicted?

18:38.617 --> 18:40.519 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM JEFFRESS: Not while he's
sitting.

18:40.552 --> 18:42.221 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That seems to be settled.

18:42.254 --> 18:48.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He can be impeached and could be
indicted
after being impeached if -- once
he's removed

18:48.760 --> 18:50.496 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
from office.

18:50.529 --> 18:53.899 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And so, Michael, this
becomes not
-- then that becomes a question
of not so

18:53.932 --> 18:59.338 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
