coordination between Russia and
the Trump
campaign.

28:21.066 --> 28:23.768 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're joined now by phone by
John Carlin.

28:23.802 --> 28:27.806 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He served as chief of staff and
senior counsel
to Robert Mueller.

28:27.839 --> 28:33.445 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's now an attorney in private
practice specializing
in cyber-security and crisis
management.

28:33.478 --> 28:35.447 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Mr. Carlin, thanks for joining
us.

28:35.480 --> 28:37.415 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Tell us a little bit about your
former boss.

28:37.449 --> 28:44.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN CARLIN, Former Justice
Department Official:
I can't think of an American of
higher integrity

28:44.122 --> 28:45.924 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and experience.

28:45.957 --> 28:53.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is someone legendary who
prosecutors
and agents in the field, who --
a former Marine,

28:53.231 --> 29:02.107 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
spent a career as a prosecutor,
has been nominated
by presidents, including
President Clinton,

29:02.140 --> 29:08.613 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Bush, and President
Obama, for different
positions, and, throughout his
career, has

29:08.646 --> 29:13.118 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
earned respect on both sides of
the aisle.

29:13.151 --> 29:16.955 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And do -- talk about
his independence.

29:16.988 --> 29:20.692 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There was -- you talked about
being legendary.

29:20.725 --> 29:27.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's -- one of the legends
about Robert
Mueller is his threat to resign,
ironically,

29:27.232 --> 29:33.838 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with then-Deputy Attorney
General James Comey
facing down the Bush
administration.

29:33.872 --> 29:44.415 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN CARLIN: He's someone who
has a firm belief
in what's right and wrong and
what the appropriate

29:44.449 --> 29:47.385 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
role of a government official
should be.

29:47.418 --> 29:53.124 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think he's someone who looks
to -- epitomizes
the idea that you should just
follow the facts

29:53.158 --> 30:00.565 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and the law, and has done so in
all the different
steps of his -- of his career.

30:00.598 --> 30:05.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, as you have referenced,
he's someone
who, if something appears that
it's outside

30:05.670 --> 30:09.674 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the law, he won't do it, or, if
it's improper,
he won't do it.

30:09.707 --> 30:13.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's that type of firm
backbone that earned
the respect of so many people
that have worked

30:13.978 --> 30:19.884 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with him as FBI agents, worked
with him as
prosecutors, and observed him
over the years.

30:19.918 --> 30:22.554 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's also highly unusual in this
age.

30:22.587 --> 30:27.192 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's someone who hates the --
and avoids the
limelight.

30:27.225 --> 30:36.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he's managed to stay out of
most news
stories and keep an unbelievably
low profile,

30:36.267 --> 30:38.736 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
when you consider what he's done
over his
career.

30:38.770 --> 30:41.673 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Could you remind us
of that episode?

30:41.706 --> 30:47.846 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Recount for us that episode with
the showdown
with, I believe, as I recall, it
was White

30:47.879 --> 30:49.948 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
House counsel Alberto Gonzales.

30:49.981 --> 30:57.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They wanted to overrule a
Justice Department
finding regarding surveillance,
as I recall.

30:57.722 --> 30:59.591 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN CARLIN: Yes.

30:59.624 --> 31:05.496 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And according to public
reporting about what
occurred there, there was a
surveillance program

31:05.530 --> 31:11.703 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that the then attorney general
-- Attorney
General Ashcroft was ill.

31:11.736 --> 31:19.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, and Deputy Attorney General
Jim Comey
had assumed the role of acting
attorney general.

31:19.277 --> 31:26.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And based on the advice he
received from lawyers
at the Office of Legal Counsel,
he found that

31:26.150 --> 31:32.257 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the program, as it was currently
being run,
wasn't lawful, and so had to be
shut down.

31:32.290 --> 31:39.063 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he learned about a visit
that was going
to be made by members of the
White House,

31:39.097 --> 31:45.370 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
including the White House
counsel, to Attorney
General Ashcroft in his hospital
bed, and

31:45.403 --> 31:46.838 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
was concerned.

31:46.871 --> 31:54.045 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so he asked Director Mueller
to accompany
him to that hospital room.

31:54.078 --> 31:58.016 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Director Mueller did so.

31:58.049 --> 32:03.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Attorney General Ashcroft said
that, as acting
attorney general, it would be
Comey's decision

32:03.554 --> 32:07.125 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as to what was lawful or not
lawful.

32:07.158 --> 32:13.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think Director Mueller,
kind of consistent
with his career, if the lawyers
at the Justice

32:13.231 --> 32:18.636 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Department say something is not
lawful, then
you can't do it, until you work
out a way

32:18.670 --> 32:20.872 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that it's within the confines of
the law.

32:20.905 --> 32:27.211 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
No matter how important the
program might
be, the law is the law.

32:27.245 --> 32:32.317 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Ironically, the
careers of James
Comey and Robert Mueller once
again intertwined.

32:32.350 --> 32:34.285 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
John Carlin, thank you very much
for joining
us.

32:34.319 --> 32:36.020 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN CARLIN: Thank you.

32:36.054 --> 32:41.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And now we turn to --
continuing
on this story, we turn to
Congressman Adam

32:41.659 --> 32:43.695 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Kinzinger, a Republican of
Illinois.

32:43.728 --> 32:46.497 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He called today for a special
counsel.

32:46.531 --> 32:52.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Representative Kinzinger, I
presume your -- well,
what's your reaction now to the
appointment

32:52.503 --> 32:54.706 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of former FBI Director Robert
Mueller?

32:54.739 --> 32:55.907 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

32:55.940 --> 32:56.708 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ADAM KINZINGER (R), Illinois:
Well, I was
surprised.

32:56.741 --> 32:58.042 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I was surprised in a good way.

32:58.076 --> 32:59.777 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think this is the right thing
to do.

32:59.811 --> 33:05.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The reason I called for it
today, with the
revelations of the supposed memo
yesterday,

33:05.483 --> 33:08.853 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the questions that have been
arising, I just
came to the realization -- and I
have always

33:08.886 --> 33:13.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
said from the beginning the
American people
deserve the facts, whatever they
are, whoever

33:13.491 --> 33:16.094 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they exonerate or whoever they
indict.

33:16.127 --> 33:18.229 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The American people deserve
that.

33:18.262 --> 33:20.031 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And this had become way too
political.

33:20.064 --> 33:24.235 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Any new story, any new piece of
information
that had come out, you know, the
left screams

33:24.268 --> 33:26.371 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
-- some on the left mention
impeachment right
away.

33:26.404 --> 33:29.440 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Some on the right would say it's
fake news.

33:29.474 --> 33:30.675 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And neither is true.

33:30.708 --> 33:33.144 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, we need to get to the bottom
of it.

33:33.177 --> 33:35.847 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We need answers, and we need
them in a nonpartisan
way.

33:35.880 --> 33:41.152 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And my hope is, this is the
beginning of the
process of saying, let's all
tack a deep breath.

33:41.185 --> 33:46.224 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Let's aggressively find out the
truth of everything
and the facts, and then we can
move ahead,

33:46.257 --> 33:49.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and the American people can have
faith again
in the institutions of
government.

33:49.660 --> 33:54.665 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Do you think this is
going to turn
the temperature down a little
bit on the Hill,

33:54.699 --> 34:00.505 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
sort of the boiling controversy
that's been
going on for the past really
couple of weeks

34:00.538 --> 34:01.506 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
now?

34:01.539 --> 34:02.573 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

34:02.607 --> 34:03.541 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ADAM KINZINGER: It's hard to
tell.

34:03.574 --> 34:05.243 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You know, truthfully, probably
not a lot.

34:05.276 --> 34:08.413 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You're going to have now an
outlet, I guess,
for this.

34:08.446 --> 34:12.483 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's -- Congress can say --
there will probably
be these investigations
continuing still in

34:12.517 --> 34:17.655 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Congress, but the majority
of the focus
will be with the special
counsel's office.

34:17.688 --> 34:20.158 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But this is a very hot-button
issue.

34:20.191 --> 34:24.662 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And any new revelation that
comes out, people
are angry or people are happy
about what they

34:24.695 --> 34:25.897 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
see or whatever.

34:25.930 --> 34:27.665 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, you're going to continue to
see that dynamic,
I think.

34:27.698 --> 34:31.702 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I think this is going to
continue to drive
news cycles and drive stories.

34:31.736 --> 34:35.506 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think this is the right
way to go for
the American people, so they can
say -- you

34:35.540 --> 34:40.111 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
know, look, notoriously, have a
very low faith
in Congress to be able to do
things in a nonpartisan

34:40.144 --> 34:42.013 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
way, because we're a partisan
body.

34:42.046 --> 34:46.617 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But to be able now to move
forward and say
we want to get to the bottom
with a very honorable

34:46.651 --> 34:48.820 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
American like Mr. Mueller, I
think, is a good
step.

34:48.853 --> 34:54.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Is this any way an
acknowledgment
that the turmoil and sort of the
back-and-forth

34:54.959 --> 34:59.730 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that you saw with the House
Intelligence Committee
trying to investigate this, that
they just

34:59.764 --> 35:04.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
could not handle this, that you
had to turn
to someone, an outsider like
this?

35:04.202 --> 35:05.436 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

35:05.470 --> 35:07.939 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ADAM KINZINGER: Well, I think,
ultimately,
it's handleable.

35:07.972 --> 35:13.010 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And whether it's the House Intel
or the Senate
Intel Committee, they do this
kind of stuff.

35:13.044 --> 35:14.579 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They have access to the
information.

35:14.612 --> 35:16.314 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They go through the process.

35:16.347 --> 35:20.785 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there's no doubt, a month or
two ago,
it got very heated, it got very
personal.

35:20.818 --> 35:22.720 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You can't have that on the Intel
Committee.

35:22.753 --> 35:26.691 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I don't necessarily know who to
throw stones
at on that, but you can't have
that on the

35:26.724 --> 35:27.959 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Intel Committee.

35:27.992 --> 35:30.761 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
What you need is a calm,
rational investigation.

35:30.795 --> 35:34.732 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This, with this special counsel
now, hopefully,
we can get that.

35:34.765 --> 35:37.535 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And, again, there will still be
a lot of passion.

35:37.568 --> 35:39.370 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Donald Trump is a very
controversial president.

35:39.403 --> 35:43.708 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
People either love him or they
don't love
him, and so you will continue to
have that.

35:43.741 --> 35:47.578 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think now people can
hopefully rest
assured that the work is going
to be done.

35:47.612 --> 35:50.948 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But they need to understand,
everybody needs
to understand this is going to
be a slow and

35:50.982 --> 35:52.717 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
deliberate process.

35:52.750 --> 35:56.654 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I guess I'm hearing it's almost
60 days to
even get a special counsel up
and running.

35:56.687 --> 36:00.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Let me talk you about
the other
controversies that have been
around this week,

36:00.124 --> 36:04.996 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the -- not -- this was topped
obviously yesterday
by the Comey memo.

36:05.029 --> 36:14.138 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, before that, we had the
allegations about
President Trump giving Israeli
intelligence,

36:14.172 --> 36:16.974 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what's reported to be Israeli
intelligence,
to the Russians.

36:17.008 --> 36:17.975 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What do you think about that?

36:18.009 --> 36:18.976 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

36:19.010 --> 36:19.977 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ADAM KINZINGER: So, I was
disappointed.

36:20.011 --> 36:21.812 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, I'm a military pilot.

36:21.846 --> 36:25.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I still serve in the Guard and
fly planes,
and I have been in since
basically after college.

36:25.750 --> 36:30.421 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we learned early that, when
it comes to
classified information -- I have
a military

36:30.454 --> 36:34.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
classification, as well as a
congressional
classification -- you have to be
very careful

36:34.158 --> 36:35.826 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with that.

36:35.860 --> 36:38.729 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, the president does have the
right to
declassify information whenever
he wants to.

36:38.763 --> 36:44.535 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Theoretically, a president could
take everything
Edward Snowden stole and release
that himself.

36:44.569 --> 36:46.204 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But it doesn't make it wise.

36:46.237 --> 36:50.808 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so if you're going to,
especially with
an adversary, talk about
something that's

36:50.841 --> 36:52.643 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
classified, you need to do two
things.

36:52.677 --> 36:55.947 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Number one, talk to the folks
that provided
that information to you and make
sure it's

36:55.980 --> 37:00.885 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
OK, and, secondly, I think put
that through
the brain trust of your national
security

37:00.918 --> 37:05.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
group, H.R. McMaster, everybody
else, to say,
hey, I want to reveal this to
the Russians

37:05.590 --> 37:09.026 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
because it may help us in our
fight with ISIS
or whatever reason.

37:09.060 --> 37:11.529 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If we can go through that
filter, I think
it would have been very
different.

37:11.562 --> 37:16.834 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it seems like -- I wasn't in
the Oval
Office -- it seems like it was
released willy-nilly.

37:16.867 --> 37:21.272 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think that's a very bad
thing, very
dangerous, and hopefully a
lesson learned

37:21.305 --> 37:23.040 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
from all this.

37:23.074 --> 37:25.943 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: How has all of this
affected your
confidence and trust in the
president?

37:25.977 --> 37:30.982 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It's a very early
administration, and we have
had all this turmoil, all these
stories going

37:31.015 --> 37:31.983 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
on.

37:32.016 --> 37:34.318 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Has this shaken your confidence
at all?

37:34.352 --> 37:36.120 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

37:36.153 --> 37:38.656 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM KINZINGER: Well, as I have
always said,
I think the policies -- as a
Republican, the

37:38.689 --> 37:43.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
policies coming out of this
administration,
the foreign policy, has been
good.

37:43.227 --> 37:47.131 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The strike on Syria was good,
pushing back
against North Korea.

37:47.164 --> 37:48.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
The words are not.

37:48.966 --> 37:52.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You know, the tweets, the early
morning kind
of Twitter rampage and some of
these other

37:52.370 --> 37:53.337 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
things aren't.

37:53.371 --> 37:55.206 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Does it shake my confidence?

37:55.239 --> 37:59.944 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Look, I think that's a pretty
boisterous thing
to say for a member of Congress
to say whether

37:59.977 --> 38:01.545 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
or not their confidence is
shaken.

38:01.579 --> 38:03.381 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I have concerns.

38:03.414 --> 38:08.219 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I know he has a great team
around him
advising him, and I hope he
takes that advice.

38:08.252 --> 38:11.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is, again -- hopefully,
this special
counsel is the beginning of
bringing the temperature

38:11.756 --> 38:13.024 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
down a little bit.

38:13.057 --> 38:15.760 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It will always be pretty hot,
but, hopefully,
we can see that.

38:15.793 --> 38:20.431 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Do you think -- are
you hopeful
that you will and -- you and
your colleagues

38:20.464 --> 38:25.636 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in the House will be able to
focus more on
the Republican agenda now than
on the president's

38:25.670 --> 38:27.071 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
tweets and other things?

38:27.104 --> 38:28.072 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

38:28.105 --> 38:29.073 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ADAM KINZINGER: Yes.

38:29.106 --> 38:30.207 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm really hopeful.

38:30.241 --> 38:31.942 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have been hopeful for while
that we can
do that.

38:31.976 --> 38:34.312 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Look, we can walk -- I hate to
use the term,
but we can walk and chew gum out
here.

38:34.345 --> 38:39.450 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, we can have these
controversies going
on, but, still, today, we just
voted on a

38:39.483 --> 38:42.853 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
bill passed unanimously for
sanctions against
Syria.

38:42.887 --> 38:44.822 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We can continue to do that work.

38:44.855 --> 38:48.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But when you have all this
basically dominating
the news cycle, it doesn't give
us an opportunity

38:48.426 --> 38:51.095 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to get our message out, whether
it's health
care, tax reform.

38:51.128 --> 38:55.199 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, frankly, then the president
of the United
States is not out selling that
agenda, too.

38:55.232 --> 38:58.469 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it takes away some key
pieces to getting
this done.

38:58.502 --> 39:00.838 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, hope springs eternal, and I
have it now.

39:00.871 --> 39:04.175 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Adam Kinzinger,
representative
from Illinois, thanks so much
for joining

39:04.208 --> 39:05.176 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
us.

39:05.209 --> 39:06.177 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

39:06.210 --> 39:07.178 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ADAM KINZINGER: Any time.

39:07.211 --> 39:09.080 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Take care.

39:09.113 --> 39:12.783 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And now we are joined
by MD-BO /Matt
Zapotosky from The Washington
Post to talk

39:12.817 --> 39:13.784 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
about this.

39:13.818 --> 39:14.919 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Matt, thanks for joining us.

39:14.952 --> 39:17.455 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think I probably butchered
your last name.

39:17.488 --> 39:18.456 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
And I apologize.

39:18.489 --> 39:20.424 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

39:20.458 --> 39:23.861 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Matt, this -- as
recently as yesterday,
the White House was saying there
was absolutely

39:23.894 --> 39:28.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
no need for a special counsel in
this case.

39:28.499 --> 39:30.868 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
From your reporting, what --
what happened?

39:30.901 --> 39:32.870 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
How did this -- what
precipitated all of this?

39:32.903 --> 39:35.573 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MATT ZAPOTOSKY, The Washington
Post: I don't
know that the White House always
knows what's

39:35.606 --> 39:38.442 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
going on inside the Justice
Department.

39:38.476 --> 39:42.747 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And, for days now, Rod
Rosenstein, who is
the deputy attorney general, had
just seen

39:42.780 --> 39:46.984 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
his reputation battered over his
role in the
Comey case.

39:47.017 --> 39:51.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You know, pressure had been
increasing on
both sides, Democrat and
Republican, for the

39:51.789 --> 39:54.558 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Justice Department to appoint an
attorney
general.

39:54.592 --> 39:58.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm sure conversations were
going on that
we're still trying to report on
between him

39:58.496 --> 40:02.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and Bob Mueller, the former FBI
director that
they appointed to be special
counsel.

40:02.600 --> 40:05.803 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And those obviously came to
fruition today,
though it's really
late-breaking.

40:05.836 --> 40:08.205 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're still trying to report out
exactly what
happened.

40:08.239 --> 40:13.210 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: But do you think --
we know there
was reporting that Rod
Rosenstein had -- was

40:13.244 --> 40:19.216 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
unhappy that the dismissal of
Comey was put
on him, that the White House was
putting it

40:19.250 --> 40:23.621 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on him, and that he may have
even threatened
to resign.

40:23.654 --> 40:26.490 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is this a way for him to try to
sort of reclaim
his reputation?

40:26.524 --> 40:29.093 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MATT ZAPOTOSKY: I think
somewhat, you know?

40:29.126 --> 40:35.299 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, I mean, look, he maybe made
some threats
or said some things to express
his unhappiness

40:35.332 --> 40:40.871 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with the way this went down, but
you can't
read his memo any other way than
to see that

40:40.905 --> 40:42.973 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
he wanted Jim Comey gone.

40:43.007 --> 40:46.744 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That was just a blistering
critique of Jim
Comey.

40:46.777 --> 40:52.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I do think he saw a lot of the
blowback and
reacted in some ways, and maybe
that is what

40:52.850 --> 40:54.218 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
led to us where we are right
now.

40:54.251 --> 40:57.354 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Let's turn to this --
the new development,
Robert Mueller.

40:57.388 --> 41:01.158 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What -- remind us who he is, his
background,
and what he brings to this.

41:01.192 --> 41:06.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MATT ZAPOTOSKY: He's a former
FBI director
who is very well-respected in
Washington.

41:06.130 --> 41:11.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Just as I sat down, a former
federal prosecutor
I know was texting me saying,
there just could

41:11.335 --> 41:13.437 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
not be a better pick.

41:13.471 --> 41:16.440 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He has a reputation of fierce
independence.

41:16.474 --> 41:22.513 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think he has some military
experience in
his background and, of course,
led the FBI

41:22.546 --> 41:24.381 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for a long time.

41:24.415 --> 41:28.486 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, you know, and what he will
do now is just
take over this investigation,
take over what

41:28.519 --> 41:30.788 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Rod Rosenstein would have done.

41:30.821 --> 41:32.122 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He could bring in his own team.

41:32.156 --> 41:34.124 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He could use FBI agents.

41:34.158 --> 41:38.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Maybe he knows some from his
time in the bureau,
but just a very well-respected
guy in Washington.

41:38.362 --> 41:40.965 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Matt, you cover the
Justice Department.

41:40.998 --> 41:47.671 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What's this done to the career
prosecutors,
the career officials, the career
lawyers at

41:47.705 --> 41:48.906 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Justice?

41:48.939 --> 41:50.574 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What's the morale been like,
from what you
can gather?

41:50.608 --> 41:52.543 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MATT ZAPOTOSKY: I think there's
some frustration.

41:52.576 --> 41:56.680 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, by and large, people are
just putting
their heads down and working.

41:56.714 --> 42:01.852 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, there's a very small
number of people,
you know, a very tight circle, I
guess I should

42:01.886 --> 42:04.722 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
say -- I don't know about small
number -- but
on this Russia stuff.

42:04.755 --> 42:08.859 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the other business of the
Justice Department
is going on.

42:08.893 --> 42:13.364 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Certainly, I don't think anybody
likes the
hit that it's given to the
Justice Department's

42:13.397 --> 42:17.301 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
reputation, but these are career
people who
are going to come in and do
their jobs every

42:17.334 --> 42:19.103 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
day.

42:19.136 --> 42:23.007 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And do you have any
sense of where
this investigation is, where it
was before

42:23.040 --> 42:24.275 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
this announcement?

42:24.308 --> 42:27.545 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATT ZAPOTOSKY: I would say now
it has probably
slowed down.

42:27.578 --> 42:32.850 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, Bob Mueller now has to
come in, decide
what he needs for a budget,
decide who he's

42:32.883 --> 42:36.887 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
going to keep on, and if he
needs to bring
in any new people.

42:36.921 --> 42:41.725 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I don't have a crystal-clear
sense of exactly
how far along they were.

42:41.759 --> 42:46.697 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think the FBI director -- the
former FBI
director said that it had
started in July,

42:46.730 --> 42:51.068 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and that's a pretty small amount
of time for
a counterintelligence case.

42:51.101 --> 42:55.573 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And now, you know, Bob Mueller
is going to
have to come in and wrap his
arms around this

42:55.606 --> 42:57.641 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and decide where to go from
here.

42:57.675 --> 43:02.112 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: The fact that it is a
counterintelligence
case and sort of the FBI and the
Justice Department's

43:02.146 --> 43:04.882 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
spy hunters, does that make it
different?

43:04.915 --> 43:07.818 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Or how does that make it
different from a
criminal investigation?

43:07.851 --> 43:10.821 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATT ZAPOTOSKY: Certainly, that
adds sensitivities
to this.

43:10.854 --> 43:14.358 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You could be talking about
clandestine sources
and methods.

43:14.391 --> 43:18.762 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
You're talking about FBI
counterintelligence
agents who have been involved in
this.

43:18.796 --> 43:22.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is just a little more
sensitive than,
say, a bank robbery, which is
something the

43:22.433 --> 43:24.168 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
FBI also investigates.

43:24.201 --> 43:27.638 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, at the end of the day,
that's not to
say it could not produce
criminal charges.

43:27.671 --> 43:30.207 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, I'm not saying we're there
that -- yet
-- excuse me.

43:30.240 --> 43:35.546 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Even in making this
announcement, Rod Rosenstein
said, said explicitly, look, I
am not saying

43:35.579 --> 43:40.050 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
this because I think we are
ready for a prosecutor
or this is ready for criminal
charges.

43:40.084 --> 43:43.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm just saying it's in the
public interest
that someone outside the Justice
Department

43:43.854 --> 43:44.955 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
oversee this thing.

43:44.989 --> 43:46.323 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: So, we are probably
still months
away?

43:46.357 --> 43:48.158 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MATT ZAPOTOSKY: I would guess,
yes.

43:48.192 --> 43:51.862 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Matt Zapotosky, who
covers the
Justice Department for The
Washington Post,

43:51.895 --> 43:52.863 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
thanks for joining us.

43:52.896 --> 43:54.865 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MATT ZAPOTOSKY: Thank you.

43:54.898 --> 43:58.502 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And now we go back to
Capitol Hill
for a Democratic perspective
this time, Representative

43:58.535 --> 44:03.307 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Adam Schiff of California, the
ranking member
on the House Intelligence
Committee.

44:03.340 --> 44:05.075 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Mr. Schiff, thanks for joining
us.

44:05.109 --> 44:08.912 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Your reaction to this news that
the Justice
Department has appointed Robert
Mueller as

44:08.946 --> 44:10.447 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the special counsel in this
case?

44:10.481 --> 44:12.249 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

44:12.282 --> 44:14.418 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF (D), California:
Well, I think
it's a very positive step, and I
applaud the

44:14.451 --> 44:16.286 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
choice of Bob Mueller.

44:16.320 --> 44:20.924 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I think he's very widely
respected by people
on both sides of the aisle,
immensely bright,

44:20.958 --> 44:22.660 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
capable person.

44:22.693 --> 44:24.428 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I think it's the right call.

44:24.461 --> 44:27.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is not to say that there
aren't good
career people at the Department
of Justice

44:27.498 --> 44:29.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that could do this.

44:29.299 --> 44:33.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, nonetheless, I think it
will have that
much more credibility in the
public eye by

44:33.504 --> 44:38.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
appointing someone in the
special counsel
position that has that added
degree of independence

44:38.242 --> 44:44.548 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from the department, still not
the full independence
that you would have had under
the old statute,

44:44.581 --> 44:49.286 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
independent counsel statute,
but, nonetheless,
I think a very solid decision.

44:49.319 --> 44:52.856 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think it ought to help
inspire confidence
in what the department is doing.

44:52.890 --> 44:55.993 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Now, how will this
work with the
investigations on the Hill?

44:56.026 --> 45:01.131 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Will your committee
investigation continue
in parallel with Mr. Mueller's?

45:01.165 --> 45:02.132 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

45:02.166 --> 45:03.967 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: Yes, absolutely.

45:04.001 --> 45:05.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's very important, I
think, for people
to understand just what this
means and what

45:05.502 --> 45:07.204 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
it doesn't mean.

45:07.237 --> 45:10.074 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The House and Senate
investigations will continue
to go forward.

45:10.107 --> 45:12.176 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We have very important oversight
responsibility.

45:12.209 --> 45:17.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, obviously, if we uncovered
facts that
we think that prosecutors ought
to know about,

45:17.214 --> 45:20.217 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
we would refer that now to the
special counsel.

45:20.250 --> 45:25.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the sense that we may need to
coordinate
our activities, because we have
parallel investigations

45:25.756 --> 45:29.426 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
running, we would now work with
Mr. Mueller.

45:29.460 --> 45:33.731 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, none of this stops what's
going on in
the House and Senate.

45:33.764 --> 45:39.269 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Indeed, if we form an
independent commission,
that also is a completely
separate mission

45:39.303 --> 45:41.105 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
than that by the special
counsel.

45:41.138 --> 45:45.609 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The special counsel will be
overseeing the
FBI agents who are working the
investigation,

45:45.642 --> 45:49.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and the special counsel will be
making decisions,
if it comes to that, whether
charges ought

45:49.780 --> 45:51.448 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to be brought and against whom.

45:51.482 --> 45:55.619 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And what will your
committee be
asking for, with this disclosure
that Mr.

45:55.652 --> 46:02.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Comey appears to have kept
contemporaneous
memos of his conversations and
dealings with

46:02.426 --> 46:04.328 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the president throughout this?

46:04.361 --> 46:06.196 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Will you be seeking those
documents?

46:06.230 --> 46:08.132 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Will you be seeking testimony
from Mr. Comey?

46:08.165 --> 46:09.533 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

46:09.566 --> 46:12.269 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: I think we will in
Congress be
seeking those documents.

46:12.302 --> 46:15.572 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Indeed, many of the chairs have
already asked
for them.

46:15.606 --> 46:19.576 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I also think it will be
important for Director
Comey to come and testify once
again, I hope

46:19.610 --> 46:25.816 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in open session, so that we can
add context
to whatever is in these written
memoranda.

46:25.849 --> 46:30.654 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If there are tapes as well, as
the president
has threatened, we ought to
obtain those.

46:30.687 --> 46:36.326 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Those, in fact, would be the
very best evidence
of the discussions that may have
taken place

46:36.360 --> 46:41.031 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
along the lines of that New York
Times report
in which it's alleged that the
president asked

46:41.064 --> 46:43.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Director Comey to drop the
investigation of
Michael Flynn.

46:43.634 --> 46:48.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, all of that work in Congress
by the House
Intelligence Committee, by the
Senate Intelligence

46:48.572 --> 46:51.175 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
