Netanyahu is a bit
intimidated of and afraid of
President Trump.

51:18.241 --> 51:24.614 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Mr. Netanyahu is doing
whatever he can
to play down this affair and not
doing anything

51:24.648 --> 51:27.484 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that could harm the president's
visit to Israel
next week.

51:27.517 --> 51:31.655 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: In your
reporting, have
you gotten any sense that
Israeli intelligence

51:31.688 --> 51:37.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is now trying to preserve or
protect or somehow
try to cover the intelligence
that they have

51:37.661 --> 51:40.497 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
already shared with the United
States because
of this?

51:40.530 --> 51:42.265 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
RONEN BERGMAN: Yes, indeed.

51:42.299 --> 51:47.170 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There is a risk assessment and
damage assessment
process going on as we speak.

51:47.204 --> 51:55.045 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the assumption, as in all
intelligence
scandals, is the worst-case
scenario, meaning

51:55.078 --> 51:58.482 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that much of the information is
in jeopardy.

51:58.515 --> 52:06.690 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Therefore, steps need to be
taken to minimize
the damage, save the lives
sources and protect

52:06.723 --> 52:10.494 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
